Kellie, you address an application by name.  So you address XEDIT with
ADDRESS XEDIT.  More precisely, every application that wishes to be
the target of an ADDRESS tells REXX what its name is and where the
entry point for such calls should be.  REXX then looks up the currently
active address (name) and transfers control to the corresponding entry
point when a command is issued to that environment (ADDRESS).   Dave

