OS/2 applications that adhere to this convention are very rare.  Most
export functionality through function libraries or by using REXX as a macro 
language.  Unfortunately, IBM provided several different ways to do the same
thing, and did not make it clear that one was more appropriate than another.

 Paul Prescod


